						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Quietust wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">There's actually two minor flaws in the sample code you posted on the Steam forums:<br />1. wParam needs to be ANDed with 0xFFF0 first.<br /><div class="quotetitle">MSDN wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">In WM_SYSCOMMAND messages, the four low-order bits of the wParam parameter are used internally by the system. To obtain the correct result when testing the value of wParam, an application must combine the value 0xFFF0 with the wParam value by using the bitwise AND operator.</div><br /></div><br />You're right -- thanks, I've updated my post on Steam.  I believe this also means the Nestopia code is wrong too (lacking <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">&amp; 0xfff0</tt>), but the <a href="https://github.com/rdanbrook/nestopia/blob/master/source/win32/NstWindowMain.cpp#L387" class="postlink">updated unofficial version in git</a> has it fixed.</div>

