						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Drag wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">SDL2 has functions for disabling the screensaver, but does anyone know how it does it?</div><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp; case WM_SYSCOMMAND:<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; {<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; /* Don't start the screensaver or blank the monitor in fullscreen apps */<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; if ((wParam &amp; 0xFFF0) == SC_SCREENSAVE ||<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; (wParam &amp; 0xFFF0) == SC_MONITORPOWER) {<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; if (SDL_GetVideoDevice()-&gt;suspend_screensaver) {<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; return (0);<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; }<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; }<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; }<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; break;<br /></div></div>

					
